Interface QueueADT<E>

Type Parameters:
E - type of element
All Superinterfaces:
Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
MyQueue
public interface QueueADT<E> extends Serializable
This is the professional Queue Interface for Object-Oriented Programming 3 (CRPG 304) at the SAIT Polytechnic. This Queue embodies all the standard Queue operations, and includes several helper methods that will give the data structure more flexibility and use.

  • Method Details

    • enqueue

      void enqueue(E toAdd) throws NullPointerException
      Enqueue will place the added item at the last position in the queue. This method will not allow null values to be added to the Queue.
      Parameters:
      toAdd - the item to be added to the Queue.
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - raised when a null object is placed in the Queue.

    • dequeue

      E dequeue() throws EmptyQueueException
      Dequeue will remove the first item that was placed in the Queue.
      Returns:
      the first item in the Queue.
      Throws:
      EmptyQueueException - raised when the queue's length is zero (0).

    • peek

      E peek() throws EmptyQueueException
      Peek provides a reference to the first item in the queue without removing from the queue.
      Returns:
      the first item in the queue.
      Throws:
      EmptyQueueException - raised when the queue's length is zero (0).

    • contains

      boolean contains(E toFind) throws NullPointerException
      Returns true if this list contains the specified element. More formally, returns true if and only if this list contains at least one element e such that (o==null ? e==null : o.equals(e)).
      Parameters:
      toFind - element whose presence in this list is to be tested.
      Returns:
      true if this list contains the specified element.
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the specified element is null and this list does not support null elements.

    • search

      int search(E toFind)
      Returns the 1-based position where an object is on this queue. If the object o occurs as an item in this queue, this method returns the distance from the front of the queue of the occurrence nearest the front of the queue; the first item on the stack is considered to be at distance 1. The equals method is used to compare o to the items in this queue.
      Parameters:
      toFind - the desired object.
      Returns:
      the 1-based position from the top of the queue where the object is located; the return value -1 indicates that the object is not on the queue.

    • equals

      boolean equals(QueueADT<E> that)
      Used to compare two Queue ADT's. To be equal two queues must contain equal items appearing in the same order.
      Parameters:

      Returns:
      true if the queues are equal.

      E[] toArray(E[] holder) throws NullPointerException
      Returns an array containing all of the elements in this list in proper sequence; the runtime type of the returned array is that of the specified array. Obeys the general contract of the Collection.toArray(Object[]) method.

    • isFull

      Returns true if the number of items in the queue equals the length. This operation is only implement when a fixed length queue is required.
